<topic id = "id131JK0S017Q"
    xmlns:ditaarch = "http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/">
<title>Set Attribute Display</title>
<shortdesc>Applies the specified attribute display setting to the
current file or book.</shortdesc>
<prolog><author>Scott Prentice</author>
<critdates><created date = "2013-01-19"/>
<revised modified = "2013-01-21"/></critdates></prolog>
<body><p>The available settings correspond to those listed in the
Attribute Display Options dialog found by right-clicking in the
Structure View window. The setting for this command is defined in
the <filepath>fm2dita.ini</filepath> file by the AttributeDisplay
parameter. Valid values are as follows:</p>
<ul><li>None</li>
<li>ReqSpec</li>
<li>All</li></ul>
<p>By default this command applies the “ReqSpec” (required and specified)
value.</p>
<p>Use this command on the newly structured files after applying
a conversion table, to make it easier to navigate the Structure
View.</p></body></topic>
